race.comment: Expecting there to be a good buzz around the debut of GUEST HOUSE (1). Had a nice grounding at the trials. Beat up the winner of the Pakenham race that is the raceday formline to the fore in this and was even better sitting wide and looking ready sharp on the Heath last time. No shock if he proved a good early running talent. FINE SIERRA (4) was third there but had looked sure to need the hit out of jump outs prior so could be a big improver now. ETERNAL JOY (6) ran in a low key race at Geelong but looked okay. BRIGHT STAR (16) was well fancied at Pakenham but too green. Should prove a good deal better than that.
